    {
      "id": "ce3abe9b_c5ee2773",
      "file_path": "Changelog.md",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 7,
      "message": "No, version update is not required for every patch; it depends on type of patch being introduced (cosmetic/non-functional/functional/bug-fix) - for latter two, generally recommend version bump. \n\nAs this is addressing OJSI security fix, separate patch recommendation makes sense here (otherwise this could have also been rolled into either 2.3.0 as it is not released)\n\nNow that we have 2.3.1 - we can focus on test/rls of this version once the change is merged",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 93,
        "name": "Vijay Venkatesh Kumar",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "vijayv81@gmail.com",
        "username": "vv770d"
      },
      "updated": "2021-06-21 13:41:15.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "feedf21c_76d3baea",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "c75b6704_082e82da",
      "file_path": "Changelog.md",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 7,
      "message": "Normally it would be. But Vijay tells me that 2.3.0 has not been released anywhere yet.\n\nSo no, a version bump was not needed for this particularly situation.\n\nBut thank you.\n\nSince you are doing other updates to this same code, you can continue using 2.3.1 for each of those until you are done.",
      "author": {
